description:
Assembly Elections 2022 LIVE: In a major setback to Arvind Kejriwal-led Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) days ahead of the Punjab Assembly elections, Union Home Minister Amit Shah has assured state chief minister Charanjit Singh Channi that he would "personally look into" allegations against the party's alleged ties with pro-Khalistan outfit Sikhs for Justice (SFJ). In a letter on Friday, Shah said “any political party seeking help from a terrorist outfit in polls is against the sovereignty and integrity of the nation.”
Meanwhile, campaigning for the third phase of the UP Assembly polls ended on Friday, with senior leaders of all parties making a last-ditch attempt to woo voters in 59 constituencies spread across 16 districts. Campaigning for the 117 Assembly seats of Punjab for a single phase polls also came to an end. Polling will begin at 7 am on Sunday and continue till 6 in the evening.
